<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="539" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,691,1184]" pageId="12" pageNumber="539">
The most characteristic property of the calling song of 
<taxonomicName box="[838,950,945,968]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Montana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="539" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tomini">
<emphasis box="[838,950,945,968]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="539">M. tomini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the extraordinarily large duration of its syllables (
<figureCitation box="[265,333,980,1005]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1911,1933]" captionTargetBox="[161,1424,210,1856]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,193,1890]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 7. Oscillograms of calling songs of Montana species. A— medvedevi, B— striata (left Romania, right Russia), C 1 — decticiformis (Shatpe 27 ° C + sun), C 2 — decticiformis (Zharmysh 20 ° C), D— taurica, E 1 — montana (Austria), E 2 — montana (Ukraine, 25 ° C), F— daghestanica, G— armeniaca, H— eversmanni (see text), I— tianshanica, J 1 — tomini (25 ° C), J 2 — tomini (16 ° C), K— helleri. See Table 2 and text for details." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/573664/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="539">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
J). At 20°C the last syllable of a bi-syllabic echeme lasted about 200 ms. Only 
<taxonomicName box="[1226,1337,980,1005]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Montana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="539" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="helleri">
<emphasis box="[1226,1337,980,1005]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="539">M. helleri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is in the same range (150 ms at 30°C). However, both species differ considerably in the number of impulses per syllable: 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Montana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="539" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="helleri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="539">M. helleri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has 32 impulses (and 39 teeth in the stridulatory file; 
<bibRefCitation author="Ciplak" box="[826,1022,1052,1077]" pageId="12" pageNumber="539" refString="Ciplak, B., Taylan, M. S. &amp; Sirin, D. (2006) Description of Platycleis (Montana) helleri sp. n. (Orthoptera, Tettigoniidae, Tettigoniinae): morphology, song and remarks on the distribution of the subgenus. Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 132 (3 - 4), 261 - 269." type="journal article" year="2006">Ciplak et al 2006</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName box="[1042,1151,1053,1076]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Montana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="539" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tomini">
<emphasis box="[1042,1151,1053,1076]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="539">M. tomini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
ca. 80 impulses (and 108 teeth; 
<figureCitation box="[222,291,1087,1112]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1461,1483]" captionTargetBox="[153,1431,773,1433]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[150,1436,766,1439]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 6. Scanning electron microscopic images of stridulatory files. A— Montana medvedevi, B— Montana montana, C— Montana tomini (scale 100 µm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/573663/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="539">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
C). Concerning the number of syllables per echeme, there is a surprising variability (
<figureCitation box="[1267,1342,1087,1112]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1911,1933]" captionTargetBox="[161,1424,210,1856]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,193,1890]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 7. Oscillograms of calling songs of Montana species. A— medvedevi, B— striata (left Romania, right Russia), C 1 — decticiformis (Shatpe 27 ° C + sun), C 2 — decticiformis (Zharmysh 20 ° C), D— taurica, E 1 — montana (Austria), E 2 — montana (Ukraine, 25 ° C), F— daghestanica, G— armeniaca, H— eversmanni (see text), I— tianshanica, J 1 — tomini (25 ° C), J 2 — tomini (16 ° C), K— helleri. See Table 2 and text for details." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/573664/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="539">Figs 7</figureCitation>
J1, 7J2). One animal (
<collectingCountry box="[303,343,1124,1149]" name="Switzerland" pageId="12" pageNumber="539">CH</collectingCountry>
5317) showed consistently always three to six (eight) syllables per echeme (cage recording at 16°C), the others only two to four.
</paragraph>
